The Emir of Ilorin and Chairman, Kwara State Council of Chiefs, Dr. Ibrahim Sulu-Gambari, has said that former Lagos State governor, Bola Tinubu, deserves to be the next president. Sulu-Gambari spoke, yesterday, when he hosted members of the South West Agenda for Asiwaju (SWAGA) in his Ilorin palace. He noted that the APC presidential aspirant has traversed Nigeria and impacted on many Nigerians. Earlier, the National Chairman of SWAGA, Senator Dayo Adeyeye, informed the monarch that they were in the state to inaugurate the North Central chapter of SWAGA to propagate the emergence of Tinubu as Nigeriaâ€™s next president. 